description: Round # 1 of the Unified Federation of Dirt season comes to Lawrence Kansas on March 24, 2013. Classic cross country racing returns to the Lawrence River Trails for a fun day of racing.

title: Bone Bender 3/6 Hour MTB Odyssey
description: The 2013 UFD’s endurance  season continues with the 5th Annual Bone Bender 3/6 Hour MTB Odyssey.  The event is permitted with USA Cycling .  Host teams are the Cow Town Cycling Team, The Wheel Cyclery and Team GO
course: The BB36 consists of a 10 to 15 mile  loop course comprised of rocky technical sections with many short power climbs.  Several areas will cross rocky stream beds. Other areas will have fast flowing sections.  All this along  the  North Shore of Clinton Lake which is ranked  among the best trail systems in the Midwest.
registration:
Register today at www.usacycling.org.  Field limit of 300 applies.  Online registration closes on 4/11/13.  There will be registration available during Saturday’s packet pickup (up to field limit) .  

Early registration fees: $35.00 for 3 hour , $50.00 for 6 hour, $60.00 per team. 
Pre-registration fees after 3/1/13: $40.00 for 3 hour, $55.00 for 6 hour and $65.00 per team
Onsite registration fees (if available) : $45.00 for 3 hour, $60.00 for 6 hour and $70 per team. 

Entry fee includes one-day license and $3.00 for insurance.  Also included in entry fee is a custom event t-shirt (if registered by 3/15/13), fully stocked aid stations and post race refreshments. 

Sorry, there are no refunds of entry fees in case of extreme weather or event postponement  The money will go to support local trail systems and  organizations that better cycling and trails in our region. Transfers are allowed until 4/11/13

title: Kansas Dirty Little Secret Mountain Bike Champions
Leawood City Park Mountain Bike Camp
Masons Midsummer Meltdown
description:
First annual Masons Midsummer Meltdown
cross country race and fundraiser

Held on the sweet “Wyco” singletrack trails.
course:
Course Description: Consisting of approximately 8 miles per lap this fun, fast and
challenging course is a mix of flowing hand benched singletrack, challenging
climbs, blazing downhills, a few fun features and a smidgen of double track
thrown in to insure plenty of passing opportunities. I guarantee this course will
put a smile on your face no matter if you’re a first time racer or grizzled veteran.
registration:
Registration: Online registration is highly recommended. Registration will be
available on race day ending 15 minutes before each starting time. Racers’
meetings will be held 10 minutes before each starting time.

Fees: Online registration for Cat 1 $30; Cat 2, 3, SS, Clyde $25; Juniors $15. Race day
registration will be an additional $5.
All proceeds from the race will go directly to the Trail Masons Association to help
build and maintain more singletrack trails for all to enjoy.
notes:
Event Notes: Wyandotte County Lake Trails are marked with an intersection
numbering system for your navigation convenience. A trail system map and course
cue sheet is available for download for your pre-ride enjoyment.

This event will be postponed to a rain date if it is believed that significant trail
damage will occur by running the race on the scheduled date.
directions:
Directions: Wyandotte County Lake Shelter #3 is easily accessed from I- 435,
just north of Kansas Speedway. From I-435 proceed east on Leavenworth road,
pass the main park entrance and take a left north on 83rd street, take a left at the
park entrance, you will take a right at the lake and then a left at the sign saying
shelters 3,5,9. Shelter #3 will be the first on your left. There will be plenty of signs
to assist you on race day. Overflow parking will be available at the main trail head
above shelter 9 just a short bike ride away.

title: Tour de Lizard Fat Tire Classic
Double Ogg Dare Dirty Time Trial
description: Test yourself against the clock in a non-competitive USA Cycling sanctioned event over Shawnee Mission Park's extensive single-track trail system. A $25 entry fee includes t-shirt, festival admission and meal.
course: 8.2 mile loop course incorporating the red, violet, and orange trail loops. Includes chip timing with immediate results on the video board.
registration:
Registration onsite is at the main festival registration table, top of Ogg Road, and closes at 11:45am.   

www.doubleoggdare.com
directions: From I435 travel to Midland Road exit in Shawnee. Head left/west to Ogg Road, go left into Park and park at the top of the road at designated parking. Attendants will direct you. From Renner Road go into main park entrance and turn right. Follow park road North around Lake to Ogg Road and turn right up Ogg Road to the event parking.

title: Wyco's Revenge Mountain Bike Race
description:
Welcome to the 2nd Annual Wyco’s Revenge Mountain Bike Race. Come challenge yourself to the full Wyco’s Revenge or the lesser Wyco’s Sprint and enjoy a fabulous evening ride into the night on what is quickly becoming “Kansas City’s Best Kept Secret”.  

What is it?: The Wyco’s Revenge is a timed mountain bike event held on off-road single track trails. The event will challenge participants both physically and mentally.  The event will start approximately  1  hour before sunset -6:00 pm.  The final laps of the Wyco’s Revenge will require lights. Participants will complete 3 laps for a total of ~25 miles.  The Wyco’s Sprint is a timed mountain bike event held on the same course with participants completing 1 lap.
course: The Wyco’s Revenge will be held on the awesome single track trails of Wyandotte County Lake Park.   The current course distance is 8+miles.  Course includes flowing single track, double track, gravel roads, a log crossing or two, and a few minor technical sections.  The course is comprised of rolling terrain along Wyandotte County Lake.  Bring out your single speed and you will flow like a pro!
registration:
Registration:
Pre-Registration highly encouraged at www.usacycling.org/register/2013-3599    
Registration opens 9/7/12 and closes 10/3/13 at 12:00 pm CDT
Early bird entry fee(s) $25.00 Wyco’s Revenge, $20.00 Wyco’s Sprint 
Regular entry fee(s) $35.00 Wyco’s Revenge, $25.00 Wyco’s Sprint
Race Day entry fee(s) $45.00 Wyco’s Revenge, $35.00 Wyco’s Sprint
All participants must fill out a USA Cycling Standard Athletes Release form - New this year “Electronic signature” accepted when registering online. You must log into your usa cycling account. If you do not have one it can be created for no cost. www.usacycling.org
Entry fee includes USAC $3.00 surcharge
This event is sanctioned through USA Cycling.
notes:
Lights will be required to complete the full Wyco's Revenge.  Event starts at 6:00 pm with sunset at 6:55 pm.  
No lights are required for the Wyco Sprint.
directions: Directions to the Venue: I-70 to 435 North,  take the Leavenworth Rd exit East.  Proceed to the main park entrance which is N 83rd ST.  Left into park on N 83rd ST.  Left onto County Lake Rd, Right onto East Drive, Left at the sign that says shelter 3,5 & 7.  Proceed to shelter 3.
